Bombsheller Leggings Checklist
Are you using the latest version of the template? Check
at bombsheller.com/blog/leggings-template.
Are your graphics in the backmost layer, “Your Artwork”?
Are your raster images at least 300 PPI, & embeded?
For help, see: bombsheller.com/artists/adobe-illustrator-
tips.html
Did you mind the Cut Zone? Your design will get cropped
along the ankle and inseam when converting to other
sizes.
Did you fill out the Design Info at the bottom of the tem
plate according to the instructions?
Did you rename the .ai file with this information?
“DesignName-V1S11.1” (V is the version # of this design.
Only change it if you’re resubmitting with edits. S is the
template #. If you’re reading this, it’s S11.1.
If you answered YES to all of the question, then your
ready to rock! Submit your design here:
http://bombsheller.com/artists/submit-designs.html
Well done; we’ll be in touch =)
Art Credit: Who produced the original graphics you’re using? Could be
you, Monet, or the graffiti artist whose mural you photographed.
Designer: What do you go by? Could be a real name or pseudonym. It
will be shown on the site and on printed leggings. Limited to alphanu
merics, periods, dashes, and spaces. This name is permanent.
DesignName: The title of this leggings design. We may change it with
out notice if the name is not unique or doesn't follow the CamelCase
convention. Search the website to check for name availability.
